        {
          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\"drivers/ata/libata-core.c\"],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\"ata_device_blacklist\", \"ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv\"],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"Samsung 860 EVO SSD experiences SEND FPDMA QUEUED (queued TRIM) timeouts. The kernel uses a device blacklist (ata_device_blacklist array in libata-core.c) to identify devices that don't properly handle queued TRIM commands and need the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag set. Samsung SSD 840 and 850 are properly listed with this flag (lines 4562-4565), but Samsung SSD 860 is missing from this list. Without the flag, the ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() function does not disable queued TRIM support, allowing problematic FPDMA QUEUED SEND commands to be issued to the device, causing timeouts. The fix requires adding a device entry for Samsung SSD 860* with ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM and ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM flags to the blacklist, consistent with other affected Samsung models.\"\n}\n",
